John Zelepos has pleaded guilty to tax evasion and financial structuring offenses . 
  The 48-year-old faces up to 15 years in prison and may be forced to pay a $500,000 fine . 
  Prosecutors say he diverted just over $567,000 from Mystic Pizza's gross receipts into his personal bank accounts and those of family members . 
  He also filed false tax returns to hide the income . 
  The restaurant was made famous in the 1988 movie 'Mystic Pizza'